# L. main publication: sensitive directory-only envelopes
# =============================================================================
#
# Sensitive contents stay ignored. These rules expose only stable directory
# boundaries to Git's matcher and never re-include a file from those trees.
# Git cannot store a truly empty directory, so the public README documents the
# directory topology; no placeholder is added to Center/, which must retain one
# local file only: Center/执行中枢.md.
#
# Do not add `!/**`, subtree-wide exceptions, dynamic run IDs, user-specific
# directory names or local Agent/cache directories here.

